  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed BT Street Hub Kiosk advertisement would represent an incongruous visual intrusion to the street scene and contribute to an unsightly proliferation and clutter of signage and street furniture in the local area that would distract from the visual amenity of the street scene. As such, the proposal would be contrary to policies D4 (Delivering Good Design) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP1 (Design quality and local character) and LP7 (Advertisements) of Hackney&#x27;s Local Development Plan LP33 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s Shopfront Design Guide SPD.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-945c53f4-7fff-afdc-d131-00a87ea3a0f5&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
